<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-15-0006 </DOCNO><TEXT>A survey is presented of the literature data on the occurrence of adverseand, particularly, anaphylactic reactions after intravenously administerediodinated contrast media, also with respect to age, sex, allergy in casehistory, previous administration of contrast media and, also, previousreactions. The presumed mechanisms of development of these reactionsare dealt with in detail. A reliable premedication is not availabe. Theindication for examination using iodinated contrast media must be carefullyconsidered and immediate and qualified resuscitation must be at hand.(author). 3 figs., 2 tabs., 36 refs.</TEXT></DOC>